        "body":  "Codex re-review: APPROVED (content; hold for CI)\n\nThe `menu_tests.rs` module doc finding is resolved at `163e1ff`: it now preserves the historical extraction note while accurately stating that MENU-SHORTCUT-DISPLAY subsequently widened the tests for accelerator display and Play/View deferral. I rechecked the touched crate for the stale \"same tests\" / old `(label, Command)` tuple prose and found no live hits.\n\nFunctional review remains clean:\n- File/Edit shortcut display strings match the live routing sources.\n- Play/View remain `None`, which correctly avoids the advisory-vs-real Play shortcut conflict and the unbound View case.\n- `menu_item` is display-only (`shortcut_text`) and does not alter command execution.\n- `lib.rs` is currently 1061 lines and has exactly one split-exemption marker; `menu_tests.rs` has none.\n- `git diff --check` is clean.\n\nCI status at re-review time: 12/13 green with `Analyze (rust)` still in progress, PR `MERGEABLE/UNSTABLE`. Content is approved; merge should wait for CodeQL rust to finish green plus explicit human authorization.\r\n",
